abstract: >
  Cross-Model Repertory Grid (CM-RG) methodology applied at frontier
  scale: 36 LLMs from 12 providers across three deployment tiers rate
  each other's anonymised advisory responses on 86,418 emergent bipolar
  constructs derived through triadic elicitation, producing 3,055,153
  ratings across 14 (task x condition) cells. Mean inter-rater Pearson
  r = 0.200 falsifies the "objective AI judge" framing; three structured
  patterns emerge - Western consensus cluster (r=0.34), calibration-tier
  effect (mid-tier over-rates), and anti-consensus periphery.
